## Phase 0: Intake — Gather Core Parameters

Execute these steps sequentially. Do NOT batch them into a single AskUserQuestion.

### Step 0A: Customer Name

Use AskUserQuestion:

> **Re-ground:** Starting a new erxes co-development proposal.
>
> **Simplify:** Who is this proposal for? Enter the company or organization name.
>
> **Examples:** XacBank, Mobicom, APU, Acme Corp

Store the response as `$CUSTOMER_NAME`.

### Step 0B: Pain Points & Objectives

Use AskUserQuestion:

> **Re-ground:** Preparing proposal for **{{CUSTOMER_NAME}}**.
>
> **Simplify:** What are the client's main pain points or goals? This shapes the Executive Summary. Be specific — "manual workflows" is better than "inefficiency".
>
> **Examples:**
> - "Manual customer onboarding, siloed data across 3 departments"
> - "High developer costs, 6-month release cycles, legacy tech debt"
> - "No CRM, spreadsheets for sales tracking, no marketing automation"

Store as `$PAIN_POINTS`.

### Step 0C: Target Product/Service

Use AskUserQuestion:

> **Re-ground:** Proposal for **{{CUSTOMER_NAME}}** addressing: *{{PAIN_POINTS}}*.
>
> **Simplify:** What will we build or optimize together? This becomes the headline of the proposal.
>
> **Examples:** Corporate Website, Loyalty Mobile App, Internal Workflow Automation, Customer Portal, AI Support System

Store as `$TARGET_PRODUCT`.

### Step 0D: Software Foundation Tier

Use AskUserQuestion:

> **Re-ground:** Proposal for **{{CUSTOMER_NAME}}** — building *{{TARGET_PRODUCT}}*.
>
> **Simplify:** Which erxes Software Foundation tier fits this client?
>
> **RECOMMENDATION:** Choose Tier 2 for most growing companies — it covers advanced marketing automation and workflows without the enterprise overhead.
>
> | Tier | Monthly Cost | Best For |
> |------|--------------|----------|
> | A) Tier 1 | $250/mo | Micro-businesses, startups, single teams |
> | B) Tier 2 | $750/mo | Growing companies, multi-department needs |
> | C) Tier 3 | $1,500/mo | Enterprise, multi-brand, heavy integrations |

Store the selection as `$SOFTWARE_TIER` and lookup cost as `$SOFTWARE_COST`.

### Step 0E: Training Buffet Tier

Use AskUserQuestion:

> **Re-ground:** Proposal for **{{CUSTOMER_NAME}}** — Software Tier: {{SOFTWARE_TIER}} (${{SOFTWARE_COST}}/mo).
>
> **Simplify:** How many team members need upskilling? The 20x Productivity Buffet gives unlimited class access per seat.
>
> **RECOMMENDATION:** Match the training tier to the software tier for symmetry and maximum value.
>
> | Tier | Monthly Cost | Seats | Best For |
> |------|--------------|-------|----------|
> | A) Tier 1 | $250/mo | Up to 10 | Small core team |
> | B) Tier 2 | $750/mo | Up to 35 | Department-wide |
> | C) Tier 3 | $1,500/mo | Up to 80 | Full organization |

Store as `$TRAINING_TIER`, `$TRAINING_COST`, and `$TRAINING_SEATS`.

### Step 0F: Calculate Totals

Compute in the session context:
- `$TOTAL_MONTHLY` = `$SOFTWARE_COST` + `$TRAINING_COST`
- `$ANNUAL_ESTIMATE` = `$TOTAL_MONTHLY` × 12

